# Advanced Nmap

A collection of advanced Nmap commands, scanning techniques, optimization tips, and professional reconnaissance workflows.

---

# Host Discovery

## Ping Scan
```bash
nmap -sn 192.168.1.0/24
```

## Skip Host Discovery
```bash
nmap -Pn target.com
```

Useful when ICMP is blocked.

---

# Port Scanning

## SYN Scan (Fast & Stealthy)
```bash
sudo nmap -sS target.com
```

## Full TCP Connect Scan
```bash
nmap -sT target.com
```

## UDP Scan
```bash
sudo nmap -sU target.com
```

## Scan Specific Ports
```bash
nmap -p 22,80,443 target.com
```

## Scan All Ports
```bash
nmap -p- target.com
```

---

# Service & Version Detection

## Detect Services
```bash
nmap -sV target.com
```

## Aggressive Detection
```bash
nmap -A target.com
```

Includes:
- OS detection
- Version detection
- Script scanning
- Traceroute

---

# OS Detection

```bash
sudo nmap -O target.com
```

---

# NSE Scripts

## Default Scripts
```bash
nmap -sC target.com
```

## Vulnerability Scan
```bash
nmap --script vuln target.com
```

## HTTP Enumeration
```bash
nmap --script http-enum target.com
```

## SMB Enumeration
```bash
nmap --script smb-enum-shares target.com
```

## FTP Anonymous Login Check
```bash
nmap --script ftp-anon target.com
```

---

# Performance Optimization

## Faster Scan
```bash
nmap -T4 target.com
```

## Very Fast Scan
```bash
nmap -T5 target.com
```

Use carefully — may miss packets.

## Reduce Retries
```bash
nmap --max-retries 2 target.com
```

## Increase Minimum Rate
```bash
nmap --min-rate 1000 target.com
```

