# Pro Tips

## 1. Use `-Pn` when hosts block ping requests

Some servers block ICMP packets but still expose services.

---

## 2. Always Run Full Port Scans

Default scans only check top 1000 ports.

```bash
nmap -p- target.com
```

---

## 3. Combine Commands for Better Results

```bash
nmap -sS -sV -O -T4 target.com
```

---

## 4. Save Every Scan

```bash
nmap -oA recon target.com
```

Useful for reporting and later analysis.

---

## 5. Use NSE Scripts

NSE can automate:
- Enumeration
- Misconfiguration detection
- Vulnerability checks

List all scripts:
```bash
ls /usr/share/nmap/scripts/
```

---

# Ethical Reminder

Use Nmap only on:
- Systems you own
- Labs
- CTFs
- Authorized targets

Unauthorized scanning may violate laws or policies.
